What is a Diode?
A diode is a two-terminal device that allows current in only one direction.
Works like a one-way switch

Terminals
Anode (+)
Cathode (−)
Working
1. Forward Bias
Current flows
Diode conducts
2. Reverse Bias
No current flows
Diode blocks current
Types of Diodes
Rectifier Diode – converts AC to DC
Zener Diode – used for voltage regulation
LED (Light Emitting Diode) – emits light
Photodiode – detects light
